title: Aishwarya Rai’s ‘Jazbaa’ box office collections rise to Rs 15.24 cr in opening weekend
text:
Other Articles POTUS gives 'free political advice to Kanye West on 2020 presidential bid Travis Browne confirms dating fellow fighter Ronda Rousey Louis Tomlinson registers his record label post 1D's hiatus announcement Aishwarya Rai Bachchan’s comeback movie ‘Jazbaa’ box office collections have risen to Rs 15.24 crore in the opening weekend.
Revealing the box office figure of ‘Jazbaa’ trade analyst Taran Adarsh tweeted, “#Jazbaa maintained a STRONG hold on Sun. Fri 4.23 cr, Sat 5.49 cr, Sun 5.52 cr. Total: 15.24 cr. India biz.”
Directed by Sanjay Gupta the film is an action thriller that also stars Irrfan Khan in the role of a police cop.
 13, 2015 10:31 pm
